          "email": "dmitry.eremin@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-11-30 15:11:45.000000000",
          "tz": 180
        },
        "subject": "LU-8964 llite: Make readahead async",
        "message": "LU-8964 llite: Make readahead async\n\nRemoved current Lustre implementation of readahead and replaced it\nwith in-kernel implementation. Adopted code for in-kernel readahead\nusage. Perform readahead requests asynchronously from current I/O.\n\nIn combination with parallelization of generic I/O this patch allows\nsignificantly improve read performance.\n\nSerial read with fake RW on server side:\nmaster (2.10.54_13):\n20971520000 bytes (21 GB) copied, 9.99935 s, 2.1 GB/s\nthis patch (2.10.54_14):\n20971520000 bytes (21 GB) copied, 7.82126 s, 2.7 GB/s\n\nStride read with fake RW on server side:           |   master    | this patch\nreads <opts> -n 64                                 | 2.10.54_13  | 2.10.54_14\n---------------------------------------------------+-------------+------------\nreads -l 256 -o 128 -s 134217728 -b 1048576 -a 128 | 318.175MB/s | 649.091MB/s\nreads -l 128 -o 64 -s 134217728 -b 1048576 -a 64   | 129.744MB/s | 857.413MB/s\nreads -l 64 -o 32 -s 134217728 -b 1048576 -a 32    | 149.868MB/s | 948.817MB/s\nreads -l 32 -o 16 -s 134217728 -b 1048576 -a 16    | 171.335MB/s | 785.450MB/s\nreads -l 16 -o 8 -s 134217728 -b 1048576 -a 8      | 165.078MB/s | 918.306MB/s\nreads -l 8 -o 4 -s 134217728 -b 1048576 -a 4       | 204.870MB/s | 840.595MB/s\nreads -l 4 -o 2 -s 134217728 -b 1048576 -a 2       | 459.216MB/s | 1118.61MB/s\nreads -l 2 -o 1 -s 134217728 -b 1048576 -a 1       | 486.409MB/s | 1002.01MB/s\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly \\\nmdtfilesystemtype=ldiskfs ostfilesystemtype=ldiskfs \\\nclientdistro=el7 ossdistro=el7 mdsdistro=el7 \\\nmdscount=2 mdtcount=4 testlist=sanity-flr,sanity-flr,sanity-flr,sanity-flr\n\nSigned-off-by: Dmitry Eremin <dmitry.eremin@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I5bf5c6bea3a89134614c2d26765e2e8f88aa8557\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/flr"
    }
